main event: A civilian reported observing two unidentified flying objects in Colorado Springs, Colorado on May 29, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were visible for approximately 30-40 minutes., The observation was made using ground visual methods., The objects were reported to have a red, orange, and green flashing light., The conclusion drawn was that the objects were likely reflections from commercial searchlights., The report is part of the Project Blue Book documentation from the U.S. Air Force.
witness description: a civilian with questionable reliability (college student)
